t a Jade mace though so I'm not THAT happy <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   ).  Reddangel is the only warrior in my group so I say &quot;grats on your new gloves Redd&quot;.  Redd says &quot;thanks&quot; and then turns around and hands the current pair of Cobalt Gaunts none of us knew she had TO MY GUILDMATE Kurtuk.<br><br>Kurtuk immediately cancels the trade and says in group &quot;who are you trying to pass your current Cobalt Gaunts to Redd?&quot;.  And she says nothing.  At this point, I snatch up the gauntlets so as to not let her give her old pair to whoever she originally intended them to and then snatch up the new pair.  Then I say ok now I'm gonna random them to the group since Redd apparently has a pair.  Someone says &quot;just the 5 of us?&quot;.  And now Redd says, &quot;uh yeah, I already have em&quot;.  So the cleric ends up winning them in the end.<br><br>After this I call out Redd and ask who she was trying to give her old cobalt gaunts to and get no answer.  We fight a few more mobs, and still she hasn't said anything.  Finally, she goes LD and doesn't come back for the rest of the evening.<br><br>To sum it all up, we had one for sure and maybe even 2 group members try to play us for fools on NBG last night.  Thankfully, this time they were caught.  NBG policy abusers are right there on the bottom with the scum of Norrath.  That is all.<br><br><br>Luvia Hoodyhoo<br>49 Paladin of Tunare (Retired)<br><br>Vinnz Clortho<br>49 Monk of Cazic<br>Forsaken Dreams <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ucarathosollathir.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Carathos Ollathir</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalRainbow.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 